      "name": "t:sections.n_guide-shedule.name",
      "settings": {
        "active": false,
        "must_read": false,
        "heading": "Schedule & Set Reminders",
        "text": "<h2>Schedule & Set Reminders</h2><p>The Qure app supports your Micro-Infusion routine by keeping everything simple.</p><p>It helps you track treatments and stay consistent over time, without needing to think about timing or schedules.</p>"
      }
    },
    "n_guide_content_RT7gWn": {
      "type": "n_guide-content",
      "blocks": {
        "quote_g9b9Uc": {
          "type": "quote",
          "settings": {
            "style": "blue",
            "text": "<p>You may experience slight redness and irritation after the treatment. <strong>This is normal</strong> and should subside within a few hours!</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "quote_g9b9Uc"
      ],
      "name": "t:sections.n_guide-content.name",
      "settings": {
        "use_own_file": true,
        "active": false,
        "must_read": false,
        "heading": "Post-Treatment Care & Tips",
        "text": "<h2>Post-Treatment Care & Tips</h2><p>After your Micro-Infusion treatment, your skin is more absorbent and sensitive. Following the right aftercare helps maximize results and minimize irritation.</p><p><strong>For the first 24 hours:</strong></p><ul><li>Stick to gentle skincare products only, such as hydrating cleansers and simple moisturizers.</li><li>Avoid makeup, sun exposure, heat (like saunas or workouts), and swimming.</li><li>Skip active ingredients like retinol, acids, or vitamin C.</li><li>Minimize touching your face - especially with unclean hands.</li></ul><p>[quote_content]</p><p>[hr]</p><p><strong>The morning after:</strong></p><ul><li>Always apply SPF 50+ to protect your skin.</li></ul><p>[hr]</p><p><strong>For the next 2-3 days:</strong></p><ul><li>Gradually reintroduce your usual skincare.</li><li>If you use exfoliants or actives (like retinol), wait 48-72 hours before applying them again.</li></ul>",
        "slides_per_view": ""
      }
    },
    "n_guide_content_qaxRRH": {
      "type": "n_guide-content",
      "blocks": {
        "quote_fqxqVq": {
          "type": "quote",
          "settings": {
            "style": "red",
            "text": "<p><strong>Only</strong> use the serums supplied with your Micro-Infusion Device. Only our serum ampoules are developed specifically for the Qure's Micro-Infusion Device.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "quote_fqxqVq"
      ],
      "name": "t:sections.n_guide-content.name",
      "settings": {
        "use_own_file": true,
        "active": false,
        "must_read": false,
        "heading": "Safety Precautions",
        "text": "<h2>Safety Precautions</h2><p>Your Qure Micro-Infusion treatment is designed to be gentle and effective — but it's important to use it correctly. </p><p>We recommend completing a patch test on an area of your skin that isn't too exposed prior to treatment, to have a better understanding of how your skin will react and the downtime you should expect.</p><h6>Do not use Micro-Infusion if:</h6><ul><li>You have active acne, open wounds, sunburn, eczema, or rosacea</li><li>You've used retinoids, acids (AHAs/BHAs), or exfoliants in the last 48 hours</li><li>You've recently had laser, filler, or chemical peel treatments (wait at least 2 weeks)</li><li>You're pregnant or breastfeeding (without consulting your doctor first)</li><li>You have a history of keloid scarring or severe skin sensitivity</li><li>You have metal allergies or any medical concern</li></ul><p>[quote_content]</p><p>[hr]</p><h6><em>Note:</em></h6><p>This treatment is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. If you have any skin conditions, are pregnant or breastfeeding, please consult with your doctor prior to treatment.</p><p>If you have metal allergies or if you have any medical concern, please consult your medical professional before using this treatment device. Any harmful consequence resulting from misuse or application to other body areas, not following instruction or any other improper applications is neither the responsibility of Qure Skincare Pty Ltd. or its affiliates.</p>",
        "slides_per_view": ""
      }
    },
    "n_guide_faq_XGzmpC": {
      "type": "n_guide-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_Ypebcp": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How quickly will I see results?",
            "text": "<p>Micro-Infusion treatment is powerful, and you'll likely notice the first results instantly, with a strong radiance boost, softer fine lines and overall a healthy, fresh complexion in the next day or two.</p><p>The more treatments you perform, the more outstanding skin benefits you'll receive.</p><p>Depending on how many treatments you complete, the results should last three to four months.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_kJGA6W": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How often can I use the treatment?",
            "text": "<p>We recommend using your Micro-Infusion treatment every 2 weeks for the best results.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_D6GhrE": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "When is the best time to perform Micro-Infusion?",
            "text": "<p>We recommend using the treatment at night before bed, due to the increase in skin's sensitivity following the treatment.</p><p>Avoid makeup, sun exposure, heat (like saunas or workouts), and swimming for 24 hours after use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_bTrpib": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "There is a lot of serum left over. Can I still use it?",
            "text": "<p>Definitely! Once you’ve completed the treatment, take the leftover serum from the device and pat it onto your face and neck. One ampoule of serum is intended for one whole treatment. </p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_YTxURq": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why isn't the serum coming out the the device when I am stamping?",
            "text": "<p>When stamping it's best to ensure the serum is at the end of the device where the needles are.</p><p>Sometimes this requires you to slightly tilt your head back or device towards the ceiling to help the serum make its way through the needles.</p><p>Another tip is to pop the lid back on the device and put it upside down again, firmly tap the end of the device a few times to help push the serum down the needles.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_KHaJDB": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I use Micro-Infusion around the eyes?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, you can!</p><p>Make sure to apply a very gentle pressure, up to your orbital bone, when stamping around the eye area. We also recommend only doing one pass in this area.</p><p>Never use Micro-Infusion on your eyelids or too close your your lash line.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_fqnyBz": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I treat my neck?",
            "text": "<p>Yes. Performing Micro-Infusion on the neck can help improve the appearance of fine lines, and rejuvenate skin.</p><p>It can target issues such as neck creases, horizontal lines, and age-related skin concerns to help enhance the overall texture, tone, and youthfulness of the skin.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_ask_plate_Dyi6FK": {
          "type": "faq_ask_plate",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Don't see your question?",
            "button_label": "Ask us",
            "button_url": "#"
          }
        }
      },
